'''Punjab Control of Organised Crime Act, ''' ('''PCOCA''') is law to be enacted by [[Punjab, India|Punjab]] state in [[India]] to combat organised crime.<ref>{{cite web|last=Naqvi |first=Saba |url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/punjab/punjab-cabinet-refuses-nod-to-pcoca/265135.html |title=Punjab Cabinet refuses nod to PCOCA |publisher=Tribuneindia.com |date=2016-07-13 |accessdate=2018-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/ht-spotlight-gunning-for-the-gangs-of-punjab-with-pcoca-video-trail-and-special-task-force/story-DOFNHbc98gkQNaOAPqa7iL.html |title=HT Spotlight: Gunning for the gangs of Punjab &#124; punjab &#124; top |publisher=Hindustan Times |date=2016-04-22 |accessdate=2018-05-06}}</ref> It is in process of approval as the Punjab Cabinet has yet not given its approval on account of few reservations about various clauses of the Act.The Act is designed on the pattern of [[Maharashtra Control of Organised Crime Act]] enacted in 1999.

